    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Generate social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress and log the results\n\n**Pattern:** Content Generation · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nGenerate social posts with Google Sheets and WordPress and log the results. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual publishing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Stamp & Shape Asset → Payload Valid? → Build the Brief → Draft with AI Writer → Refine with AI Editor → Convert to HTML → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to content generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating publishing in content creation\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2; WordPress credentials.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "5e02f752-7814-37ab-a47b-8c00a73fab09",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "bf47cd97-36f0-fe97-7a4c-a7decbfdb528",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "fe9b9c3c-385f-6aaa-4333-1cd310f9edad",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your publishing process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
